Dimensionality Reduction¶

Try to reduce the dimensionality check the model with:

  • ['A', 'B', 'E', 'F', 'G', 'I']
  • ['A', 'C', 'D', 'F', 'G', 'I']
  • ['A', 'E', 'F', 'G', 'I']
  • ['B', 'E', 'F']
In [28]:
X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = sm.train_test_split(df[['A', 'B', 'E', 'F', 'G', 'I']], df['Target'], test_size=0.33,random_state=101)
In [29]:

Use itertools.combination to find the minimum set of features to get a score > 0.95
hint for using itertools:

In [30]:
import itertools
In [31]:
l = itertools.combinations([1,2,3,4],3)
for i in l:
    print(i)

(1, 2, 3)
(1, 2, 4)
(1, 3, 4)
(2, 3, 4)
In [32]:
for i in range(1,9):
    c = itertools.combinations("ABCDEFGI",i)
    for item in c:
        ls = list(item) 
        X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = sm.train_test_split(df[ls], df['Target'], test_size=0.33,random_state=101)
        model = sl.LinearRegression()
        model.fit(X_train,y_train)
        score = model.score(X_test,y_test)
        y_pred = model.predict(X_test)
        RMSE = np.sqrt(metrics.mean_squared_error(y_test, y_pred))
#         print(ls,score)
        if score > 0.95:
            print(ls,"    R^2 on the Test set is:, {:.4%}".format(score),"     RMSE is:", round(RMSE,3))
